# Random Beep Extension Overview

Random Beep is a browser extension that implements a unique focus methodology with random short breaks during short periods, followed by longer planned breaks after extended sessions.

## Key Components

- **Background Service**: Main extension logic that runs in the background
  - Entry point: [background/background.js](mdc:background/background.js)
  - Timer logic: [background/timer.js](mdc:background/timer.js)
  - Break generation: [background/break-generator.js](mdc:background/break-generator.js)
  - Notifications: [background/notification.js](mdc:background/notification.js)

- **User Interface**:
  - Main popup: [popup/popup.html](mdc:popup/popup.html) and [popup/popup.js](mdc:popup/popup.js)
  - Settings page: [options/options.html](mdc:options/options.html) and [options/options.js](mdc:options/options.js)
  - Statistics page: [statistics/statistics.html](mdc:statistics/statistics.html) and [statistics/statistics.js](mdc:statistics/statistics.js)

- **Data Management**:
  - Settings: [storage/settings.js](mdc:storage/settings.js)
  - Session state: [storage/session.js](mdc:storage/session.js)
  - Statistics tracking: [storage/statistics.js](mdc:storage/statistics.js)

## Extension Configuration

The extension is configured in [manifest.json](mdc:manifest.json), which defines the extension's structure, permissions, and entry points.
